2/ Quote pairs are a model originally pioneered by @virtuals_io, the model is simple: 

When you originate new coins you set the quote currency as your own token.

You token gate your markets and capture the net value of all of the coins originated.

$ZORA uses this model today https://t.co/Xzm6BmHEGH

3/ Quote pairing does not need to have any negative UX impact. 

Apps can use routing to allow users to still trade using whatever they have in their wallet. 

E.g. even though this coin is paired in $zora, users can buy using ETH, USDC or any other token. https://t.co/spaVjUcp91

5/ In the context of @zora—where we are tokenizing all content—it's likely that we can push this quote model much further to create new connections between content, memes and creators.
